; FOUND by P4 stress harness 2026-07-02 (ledger ESH-0101). XKNOWN.
;
; Plain non-tail user recursion past ~270k frames dies with SIGILL and NO
; diagnostic. The runtime depth guard (ESHKOL_MAX_RECURSION_DEPTH=100000 in
; lib/core/runtime_list_helpers.cpp) never fires for this code path - it only
; guards runtime list helpers - so the failure mode is a silent trap instead
; of "maximum recursion depth exceeded".
;
; Measured 2026-07-02 (master 2692ca63, macOS arm64):
;   depth 260000 -> OK (JIT and AOT)
;   depth 270000 -> SIGILL rc 132, no output (JIT)
;   depth 280000 -> SIGILL (AOT)
; Passing depth is pinned by rec_deep_nontco_250k.esk. This file asserts the
; aspirational behavior (either complete or diagnose); it XPASSes if stacks
; grow or segmented/guarded recursion lands.
(define (down n)
  (if (= n 0) 0 (+ 1 (down (- n 1)))))
(display "OK ") (display (down 300000)) (newline)
